---
import Footer from "../components/Footer.astro";
import Nav from "../components/Nav.astro";
import { site } from "../data/site";
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";

const title = "About AppCubic | Applied AI Venture Studio";
const description =
  "AppCubic is an applied AI venture studio for agentic systems, research-to-product workflows, and technical advisory work with technical partners.";
---

<BaseLayout title={title} description={description} pathname="/about/">
  <Nav />
  <main class="page-main">
    <div class="page-shell">
      <p class="section-label">About</p>
      <h1 class="page-title">An applied AI venture studio for technical partners.</h1>
      <p class="page-lede">
        AppCubic started in 2019 as a practical builder and operator vehicle. It now serves as the
        studio layer for applied AI products, research workflows, and technically grounded advisory work.
      </p>

      <div class="content">
        <p>
          The work is intentionally close to implementation. AppCubic is interested in systems that
          survive contact with real workflows: LLM orchestration with tool boundaries, evaluation
          loops, data movement, user-facing product surfaces, and the operational choices that make
          a prototype worth continuing.
        </p>

        <h2>What AppCubic builds around</h2>
        <p>
          The studio draws from several streams of work: e-commerce and logistics systems, technical
          advisory for early teams, LLM decision-support products, camera-based motion understanding,
          and research tooling. The common thread is not a vertical label. It is the habit of turning
          uncertain technical work into a concrete operating surface.
        </p>

        <h2>How the work is framed</h2>
        <p>
          AppCubic treats AI as infrastructure for decisions and workflows, not as a decorative
          feature. Useful systems need retrieval and context design, model-evaluation discipline,
          clear human review points, and enough product judgment to know when automation should stop.
        </p>

        <h2>Where to go next</h2>
        <p>
          Research-oriented systems live at <a href={site.links.research}>research.appcubic.com</a>.
          Adjacent product and operations work connects through <a href={site.links.futur}>Futur</a>.
          Personal background remains available at <a href={site.links.benji}>Benji's site</a>.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </main>
  <Footer />
</BaseLayout>
